var book = {
	"name": "Mark",
	"numChapters": 16,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24217A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24217A\"></sup>the Son of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24218B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24218B\"></sup>As it is written in Isaiah the prophet:“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24218C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24218C\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Behold</span>, I <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">send My messenger</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">ahead of You</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Who will prepare Your way</span>;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24219D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24219D\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The voice of one crying in the wilderness</span>,‘<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Make ready the way of the Lord</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Make His paths straight</span>.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>John the Baptist appeared in the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24220E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24220E\"></sup>preaching a baptism of repentance for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24220F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24220F\"></sup>forgiveness of sins.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And all the country of Judea was going out to him, and all the people of Jerusalem; and they were being baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>John was clothed with camel’s hair and <i>wore</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24222G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24222G\"></sup>a leather belt around his waist, and his diet was locusts and wild honey.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he was preaching, and saying, “After me One is coming who is mightier than I, and I am not fit to stoop down and untie the thong of His sandals.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I baptized you with water; but He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24225H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24225H\"></sup>In those days Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24225I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24225I\"></sup>came from Nazareth in Galilee and was baptized by John in the Jordan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Immediately coming up out of the water, He saw the heavens opening, and the Spirit like a dove descending upon Him;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and a voice came out of the heavens: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24227J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24227J\"></sup>You are My beloved Son, in You I am well-pleased.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24228K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24228K\"></sup>Immediately the Spirit *impelled Him <i>to go</i> out into the wilderness.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He was in the wilderness forty days being tempted by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24229L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24229L\"></sup>Satan; and He was with the wild beasts, and the angels were ministering to Him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24230M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24230M\"></sup>Now after John had been taken into custody, Jesus came into Galilee, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24230N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24230N\"></sup>preaching the gospel of God,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24231O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24231O\"></sup>The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24231P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24231P\"></sup>repent and believe in the gospel.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24232Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24232Q\"></sup>As He was going along by the Sea of Galilee, He saw Simon and Andrew, the brother of Simon, casting a net in the sea; for they were fishermen.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Follow Me, and I will make you become fishers of men.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Immediately they left their nets and followed Him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Going on a little farther, He saw James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, who were also in the boat mending the nets.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Immediately He called them; and they left their father Zebedee in the boat with the hired servants, and went away to follow Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24237R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24237R\"></sup>They *went into Capernaum; and immediately on the Sabbath <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24237S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24237S\"></sup>He entered the synagogue and <i>began</i> to teach.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24238T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24238T\"></sup>They were amazed at His teaching; for He was teaching them as <i>one</i> having authority, and not as the scribes.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Just then there was a man in their synagogue with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24240U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24240U\"></sup>What business do we have with each other, Jesus of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24240V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24240V\"></sup>Nazareth? Have You come to destroy us? I know who You are—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24240W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24240W\"></sup>the Holy One of God!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Jesus rebuked him, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Be quiet, and come out of him!”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Throwing him into convulsions, the unclean spirit cried out with a loud voice and came out of him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They were all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24243X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24243X\"></sup>amazed, so that they debated among themselves, saying, “What is this? A new teaching with authority! He commands even the unclean spirits, and they obey Him.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Immediately the news about Him spread everywhere into all the surrounding district of Galilee.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24245Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24245Y\"></sup>And immediately after they came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24245Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24245Z\"></sup>out of the synagogue, they came into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Simon’s mother-in-law was lying sick with a fever; and immediately they *spoke to Jesus about her.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And He came to her and raised her up, taking her by the hand, and the fever left her, and she waited on them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24248AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24248AA\"></sup>When evening came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24248AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24248AB\"></sup>after the sun had set, they <i>began</i> bringing to Him all who were ill and those who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24248AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24248AC\"></sup>demon-possessed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the whole <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24249AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24249AD\"></sup>city had gathered at the door.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24250AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24250AE\"></sup>healed many who were ill with various diseases, and cast out many demons; and He was not permitting the demons to speak, because they knew who He was.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24251AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24251AF\"></sup>In the early morning, while it was still dark, Jesus got up, left <i>the house</i>, and went away to a secluded place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24251AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24251AG\"></sup>was praying there.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Simon and his companions searched for Him;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>they found Him, and *said to Him, “Everyone is looking for You.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Let us go somewhere else to the towns nearby, so that I may preach there also; for that is what I came for.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24255AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24255AH\"></sup>And He went into their synagogues throughout all Galilee, preaching and casting out the demons.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24256AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24256AI\"></sup>And a leper *came to Jesus, beseeching Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24256AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24256AJ\"></sup>falling on his knees before Him, and saying, “If You are willing, You can make me clean.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Moved with compassion, Jesus stretched out His hand and touched him, and *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“I am willing; be cleansed.”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Immediately the leprosy left him and he was cleansed.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And He sternly warned him and immediately sent him away,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and He *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24260AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24260AK\"></sup>See that you say nothing to anyone; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24260AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24260AL\"></sup>go, show yourself to the priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24260AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24260AM\"></sup>offer for your cleansing what Moses commanded, as a testimony to them.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But he went out and began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24261AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24261AN\"></sup>proclaim it freely and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24261AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24261AO\"></sup>spread the news around, to such an extent that Jesus could no longer publicly enter a city, but stayed out in unpopulated areas; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24261AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24261AP\"></sup>they were coming to Him from everywhere."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>When He had come back to Capernaum several days afterward, it was heard that He was at home.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24263A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24263A\"></sup>many were gathered together, so that there was no longer room, not even near the door; and He was speaking the word to them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24264B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24264B\"></sup>And they *came, bringing to Him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24264C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24264C\"></sup>paralytic, carried by four men.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Being unable to get to Him because of the crowd, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24265D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24265D\"></sup>removed the roof above Him; and when they had dug an opening, they let down the pallet on which the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24265E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24265E\"></sup>paralytic was lying.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Jesus seeing their faith *said to the paralytic, <span class=\"woj\">“Son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24266F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24266F\"></sup>your sins are forgiven.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But some of the scribes were sitting there and reasoning in their hearts,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Why does this man speak that way? He is blaspheming; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24268G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24268G\"></sup>who can forgive sins but God alone?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Immediately Jesus, aware in His spirit that they were reasoning that way within themselves, *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you reasoning about these things in your hearts?</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Which is easier, to say to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24270H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24270H\"></sup>paralytic, ‘Your sins are forgiven’; or to say, ‘Get up, and pick up your pallet and walk’?</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But so that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins”</span>—He *said to the paralytic,",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“I say to you, get up, pick up your pallet and go home.”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he got up and immediately picked up the pallet and went out in the sight of everyone, so that they were all amazed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24273I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24273I\"></sup>were glorifying God, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24273J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24273J\"></sup>We have never seen anything like this.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He went out again by the seashore; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24274K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24274K\"></sup>all the people were coming to Him, and He was teaching them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24275L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24275L\"></sup>As He passed by, He saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24275M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24275M\"></sup>Levi the <i>son</i> of Alphaeus sitting in the tax booth, and He *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24275N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24275N\"></sup>Follow Me!”</span> And he got up and followed Him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And it *happened that He was reclining <i>at the table</i> in his house, and many tax collectors and sinners were dining with Jesus and His disciples; for there were many of them, and they were following Him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24277O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24277O\"></sup>the scribes of the Pharisees saw that He was eating with the sinners and tax collectors, they said to His disciples, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24277P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24277P\"></sup>Why is He eating and drinking with tax collectors and sinners?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And hearing <i>this</i>, Jesus *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24278Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24278Q\"></sup><i>It is</i> not those who are healthy who need a physician, but those who are sick; I did not come to call the righteous, but sinners.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24279R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24279R\"></sup>John’s disciples and the Pharisees were fasting; and they *came and *said to Him, “Why do John’s disciples and the disciples of the Pharisees fast, but Your disciples do not fast?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“While the bridegroom is with them, the attendants of the bridegroom cannot fast, can they? So long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24281S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24281S\"></sup>days will come when the bridegroom is taken away from them, and then they will fast in that day.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“No one sews a patch of unshrunk cloth on an old garment; otherwise the patch pulls away from it, the new from the old, and a worse tear results.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>No one puts new wine into old wineskins; otherwise the wine will burst the skins, and the wine is lost and the skins <i>as well</i>; but <i>one puts</i> new wine into fresh wineskins.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24284T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24284T\"></sup>And it happened that He was passing through the grainfields on the Sabbath, and His disciples began to make their way along while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24284U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24284U\"></sup>picking the heads <i>of grain</i>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The Pharisees were saying to Him, “Look, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24285V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24285V\"></sup>why are they doing what is not lawful on the Sabbath?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Have you never read what David did when he was in need and he and his companions became hungry;</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>how he entered the house of God in the time of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24287W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24287W\"></sup>Abiathar <i>the</i> high priest, and ate the consecrated bread, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24287X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24287X\"></sup>is not lawful for <i>anyone</i> to eat except the priests, and he also gave it to those who were with him?”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24288Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24288Y\"></sup>The Sabbath was made for man, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24288Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24288Z\"></sup>not man for the Sabbath.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the Son of Man is Lord even of the Sabbath.”</span>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24290A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24290A\"></sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24290B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24290B\"></sup>entered again into a synagogue; and a man was there whose hand was withered.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24291C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24291C\"></sup>They were watching Him <i>to see</i> if He would heal him on the Sabbath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24291D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24291D\"></sup>so that they might accuse Him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He *said to the man with the withered hand, <span class=\"woj\">“Get up and come forward!”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Is it lawful to do good or to do harm on the Sabbath, to save a life or to kill?”</span> But they kept silent.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>After <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24294E\"></sup>looking around at them with anger, grieved at their hardness of heart, He *said to the man, <span class=\"woj\">“Stretch out your hand.”</span> And he stretched it out, and his hand was restored.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Pharisees went out and immediately <i>began</i> conspiring with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24295F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24295F\"></sup>Herodians against Him, <i>as to</i> how they might destroy Him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24296G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24296G\"></sup>Jesus withdrew to the sea with His disciples; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24296H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24296H\"></sup>a great multitude from Galilee followed; and <i>also</i> from Judea,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and from Jerusalem, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24297I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24297I\"></sup>Idumea, and beyond the Jordan, and the vicinity of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24297J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24297J\"></sup>Tyre and Sidon, a great number of people heard of all that He was doing and came to Him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24298K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24298K\"></sup>And He told His disciples that a boat should stand ready for Him because of the crowd, so that they would not crowd Him;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>for He had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24299L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24299L\"></sup>healed many, with the result that all those who had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24299M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24299M\"></sup>afflictions pressed around Him in order to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24299N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24299N\"></sup>touch Him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whenever the unclean spirits saw Him, they would fall down before Him and shout, “You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24300O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24300O\"></sup>the Son of God!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24301P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24301P\"></sup>earnestly warned them not to tell who He was.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He *went up on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24302Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24302Q\"></sup>the mountain and *<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24302R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24302R\"></sup>summoned those whom He Himself wanted, and they came to Him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And He appointed twelve, so that they would be with Him and that He <i>could</i> send them out to preach,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and to have authority to cast out the demons.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And He appointed the twelve: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24305S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24305S\"></sup>Simon (to whom He gave the name Peter),",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and James, the <i>son</i> of Zebedee, and John the brother of James (to them He gave the name Boanerges, which means, “Sons of Thunder”);",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Zealot;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and Judas Iscariot, who betrayed Him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And He *came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24309T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24309T\"></sup>home, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24309U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24309U\"></sup>crowd *gathered again, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24309V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24309V\"></sup>to such an extent that they could not even eat a meal.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24310W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24310W\"></sup>His own people heard <i>of this</i>, they went out to take custody of Him; for they were saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24310X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24310X\"></sup>He has lost His senses.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The scribes who came down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24311Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24311Y\"></sup>from Jerusalem were saying, “He is possessed by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24311Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24311Z\"></sup>Beelzebul,” and “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24311AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24311AA\"></sup>He casts out the demons by the ruler of the demons.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24312AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24312AB\"></sup>And He called them to Himself and began speaking to them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24312AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24312AC\"></sup>parables, <span class=\"woj\">“How can <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24312AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24312AD\"></sup>Satan cast out Satan?</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If a kingdom is divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If a house is divided against itself, that house will not be able to stand.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24315AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24315AE\"></sup>Satan has risen up against himself and is divided, he cannot stand, but he is finished!</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24316AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24316AF\"></sup>But no one can enter the strong man’s house and plunder his property unless he first binds the strong man, and then he will plunder his house.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24317AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24317AG\"></sup>Truly I say to you, all sins shall be forgiven the sons of men, and whatever blasphemies they utter;</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24318AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24318AH\"></sup>whoever blasphemes against the Holy Spirit never has forgiveness, but is guilty of an eternal sin”</span>—",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>because they were saying, “He has an unclean spirit.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24320AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24320AI\"></sup>Then His mother and His brothers *arrived, and standing outside they sent <i>word</i> to Him and called Him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>A crowd was sitting around Him, and they *said to Him, “Behold, Your mother and Your brothers are outside looking for You.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Answering them, He *said, <span class=\"woj\">“Who are My mother and My brothers?”</span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Looking about at those who were sitting around Him, He *said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24323AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24323AJ\"></sup>Behold My mother and My brothers!</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>For whoever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24324AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24324AK\"></sup>does the will of God, he is My brother and sister and mother.”</span>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24325A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24325A\"></sup>He began to teach again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24325B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24325B\"></sup>by the sea. And such a very large crowd gathered to Him that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24325C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24325C\"></sup>He got into a boat in the sea and sat down; and the whole crowd was by the sea on the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And He was teaching them many things in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24326D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24326D\"></sup>parables, and was saying to them in His teaching,",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Listen <i>to this</i>! Behold, the sower went out to sow;</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>as he was sowing, some <i>seed</i> fell beside the road, and the birds came and ate it up.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Other <i>seed</i> fell on the rocky <i>ground</i> where it did not have much soil; and immediately it sprang up because it had no depth of soil.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And after the sun had risen, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Other <i>seed</i> fell among the thorns, and the thorns came up and choked it, and it yielded no crop.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Other <i>seeds</i> fell into the good soil, and as they grew up and increased, they yielded a crop and produced thirty, sixty, and a hundredfold.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And He was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24333E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24333E\"></sup>He who has ears to hear, let him hear.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As soon as He was alone, His followers, along with the twelve, <i>began</i> asking Him <i>about</i> the parables.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“To you has been given the mystery of the kingdom of God, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24335F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24335F\"></sup>those who are outside get everything <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24335G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24335G\"></sup>in parables,</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24336H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24336H\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">while seeing, they may see and not perceive, and while hearing, they may hear and not understand, otherwise they might return and be forgiven</span>.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24337I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24337I\"></sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you not understand this parable? How will you understand all the parables?</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sower sows the word.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are the ones who are beside the road where the word is sown; and when they hear, immediately <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24339J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24339J\"></sup>Satan comes and takes away the word which has been sown in them.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In a similar way these are the ones on whom seed was sown on the rocky <i>places</i>, who, when they hear the word, immediately receive it with joy;</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and they have no <i>firm</i> root in themselves, but are <i>only</i> temporary; then, when affliction or persecution arises because of the word, immediately they fall away.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And others are the ones on whom seed was sown among the thorns; these are the ones who have heard the word,</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>but the worries of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24343K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24343K\"></sup>the world, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24343L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24343L\"></sup>deceitfulness of riches, and the desires for other things enter in and choke the word, and it becomes unfruitful.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And those are the ones on whom seed was sown on the good soil; and they hear the word and accept it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24344M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24344M\"></sup>bear fruit, thirty, sixty, and a hundredfold.”</span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24345N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24345N\"></sup>A lamp is not brought to be put under a basket, is it, or under a bed? Is it not <i>brought</i> to be put on the lampstand?</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24346O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24346O\"></sup>For nothing is hidden, except to be revealed; nor has <i>anything</i> been secret, but that it would come to light.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24347P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24347P\"></sup>If anyone has ears to hear, let him hear.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Take care what you listen to. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24348Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24348Q\"></sup>By your standard of measure it will be measured to you; and more will be given you besides.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24349R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24349R\"></sup>For whoever has, to him <i>more</i> shall be given; and whoever does not have, even what he has shall be taken away from him.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And He was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“The kingdom of God is like a man who casts seed upon the soil;</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and he goes to bed at night and gets up by day, and the seed sprouts and grows—how, he himself does not know.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The soil produces crops by itself; first the blade, then the head, then the mature grain in the head.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But when the crop permits, he immediately <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24353S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24353S\"></sup>puts in the sickle, because the harvest has come.”</span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24354T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24354T\"></sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“How shall we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24354U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24354U\"></sup>picture the kingdom of God, or by what parable shall we present it?</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><i>It is</i> like a mustard seed, which, when sown upon the soil, though it is smaller than all the seeds that are upon the soil,</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>yet when it is sown, it grows up and becomes larger than all the garden plants and forms large branches; so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24356V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24356V\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the birds of the</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">air</span> can <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">nest under its shade</span>.”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>With many such parables He was speaking the word to them, so far as they were able to hear it;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and He did not speak to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24358W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24358W\"></sup>without a parable; but He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24358X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24358X\"></sup>explaining everything privately to His own disciples.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24359Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24359Y\"></sup>On that day, when evening came, He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Let us go over to the other side.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Leaving the crowd, they *took Him along with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24360Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24360Z\"></sup>in the boat, just as He was; and other boats were with Him.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And there *arose a fierce gale of wind, and the waves were breaking over the boat so much that the boat was already filling up.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Jesus Himself was in the stern, asleep on the cushion; and they *woke Him and *said to Him, “Teacher, do You not care that we are perishing?”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And He got up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24363AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24363AA\"></sup>rebuked the wind and said to the sea, <span class=\"woj\">“Hush, be still.”</span> And the wind died down and it became perfectly calm.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you afraid? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24364AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24364AB\"></sup>Do you still have no faith?”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>They became very much afraid and said to one another, “Who then is this, that even the wind and the sea obey Him?”"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24366A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24366A\"></sup>They came to the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gerasenes.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When He got out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24367B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24367B\"></sup>the boat, immediately a man from the tombs <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24367C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24367C\"></sup>with an unclean spirit met Him,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and he had his dwelling among the tombs. And no one was able to bind him anymore, even with a chain;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>because he had often been bound with shackles and chains, and the chains had been torn apart by him and the shackles broken in pieces, and no one was strong enough to subdue him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Constantly, night and day, he was screaming among the tombs and in the mountains, and gashing himself with stones.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Seeing Jesus from a distance, he ran up and bowed down before Him;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and shouting with a loud voice, he *said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24372D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24372D\"></sup>What business do we have with each other, Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24372E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24372E\"></sup>Son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24372F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24372F\"></sup>the Most High God? I implore You by God, do not torment me!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For He had been saying to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Come out of the man, you unclean spirit!”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And He was asking him, <span class=\"woj\">“What is your name?”</span> And he *said to Him, “My name is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24374G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24374G\"></sup>Legion; for we are many.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he <i>began</i> to implore Him earnestly not to send them out of the country.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now there was a large herd of swine feeding nearby on the mountain.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><i>The demons</i> implored Him, saying, “Send us into the swine so that we may enter them.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesus gave them permission. And coming out, the unclean spirits entered the swine; and the herd rushed down the steep bank into the sea, about two thousand <i>of them</i>; and they were drowned in the sea.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Their herdsmen ran away and reported it in the city and in the country. And <i>the people</i> came to see what it was that had happened.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They *came to Jesus and *observed the man who had been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24380H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24380H\"></sup>demon-possessed sitting down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24380I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24380I\"></sup>clothed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24380J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24380J\"></sup>in his right mind, the very man who had had the “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24380K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24380K\"></sup>legion”; and they became frightened.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Those who had seen it described to them how it had happened to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24381L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24381L\"></sup>demon-possessed man, and <i>all</i> about the swine.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24382M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24382M\"></sup>implore Him to leave their region.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24383N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24383N\"></sup>As He was getting into the boat, the man who had been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24383O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24383O\"></sup>demon-possessed was imploring Him that he might accompany Him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And He did not let him, but He *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24384P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24384P\"></sup>Go home to your people and report to them what great things the Lord has done for you, and <i>how</i> He had mercy on you.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he went away and began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24385Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24385Q\"></sup>proclaim in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24385R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24385R\"></sup>Decapolis what great things Jesus had done for him; and everyone was amazed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24386S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24386S\"></sup>When Jesus had crossed over again in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24386T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24386T\"></sup>the boat to the other side, a large crowd gathered around Him; and so He stayed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24386U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24386U\"></sup>by the seashore.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24387V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24387V\"></sup>One of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24387W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24387W\"></sup>the synagogue officials named Jairus *came up, and on seeing Him, *fell at His feet",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and *implored Him earnestly, saying, “My little daughter is at the point of death; <i>please</i> come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24388X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24388X\"></sup>lay Your hands on her, so that she will get well and live.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And He went off with him; and a large crowd was following Him and pressing in on Him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>A woman who had had a hemorrhage for twelve years,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and had endured much at the hands of many physicians, and had spent all that she had and was not helped at all, but rather had grown worse—",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>after hearing about Jesus, she came up in the crowd behind <i>Him</i> and touched His cloak.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For she thought, “If I just touch His garments, I will get well.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Immediately the flow of her blood was dried up; and she felt in her body that she was healed of her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24394Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24394Y\"></sup>affliction.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Immediately Jesus, perceiving in Himself that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24395Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24395Z\"></sup>the power <i>proceeding</i> from Him had gone forth, turned around in the crowd and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Who touched My garments?”</span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And His disciples said to Him, “You see the crowd pressing in on You, and You say, ‘Who touched Me?’”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And He looked around to see the woman who had done this.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But the woman fearing and trembling, aware of what had happened to her, came and fell down before Him and told Him the whole truth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And He said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Daughter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24399AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24399AA\"></sup>your faith has made you well; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24399AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24399AB\"></sup>go in peace and be healed of your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24399AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24399AC\"></sup>affliction.”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>While He was still speaking, they *came from the <i>house of</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24400AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24400AD\"></sup>synagogue official, saying, “Your daughter has died; why trouble the Teacher anymore?”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But Jesus, overhearing what was being spoken, *said to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24401AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24401AE\"></sup>synagogue official, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24401AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24401AF\"></sup>Do not be afraid <i>any longer</i>, only believe.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And He allowed no one to accompany Him, except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24402AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24402AG\"></sup>Peter and James and John the brother of James.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>They *came to the house of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24403AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24403AH\"></sup>synagogue official; and He *saw a commotion, and <i>people</i> loudly weeping and wailing.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And entering in, He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why make a commotion and weep? The child has not died, but is asleep.”</span>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They <i>began</i> laughing at Him. But putting them all out, He *took along the child’s father and mother and His own companions, and *entered <i>the room</i> where the child was.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Taking the child by the hand, He *said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Talitha kum!”</span> (which translated means, <span class=\"woj\">“Little girl, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24406AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24406AI\"></sup>I say to you, get up!”</span>).",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Immediately the girl got up and <i>began</i> to walk, for she was twelve years old. And immediately they were completely astounded.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24408AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24408AJ\"></sup>gave them strict orders that no one should know about this, and He said that <i>something</i> should be given her to eat."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24409A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24409A\"></sup>Jesus went out from there and *came into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24409B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24409B\"></sup>His hometown; and His disciples *followed Him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When the Sabbath came, He began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24410C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24410C\"></sup>to teach in the synagogue; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24410D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24410D\"></sup>many listeners were astonished, saying, “Where did this man <i>get</i> these things, and what is <i>this</i> wisdom given to Him, and such miracles as these performed by His hands?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Is not this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24411E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24411E\"></sup>the carpenter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24411F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24411F\"></sup>the son of Mary, and brother of James and Joses and Judas and Simon? Are not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24411G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24411G\"></sup>His sisters here with us?” And they took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24411H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24411H\"></sup>offense at Him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24412I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24412I\"></sup>A prophet is not without honor except in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24412J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24412J\"></sup>his hometown and among his <i>own</i> relatives and in his <i>own</i> household.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And He could do no miracle there except that He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24413K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24413K\"></sup>laid His hands on a few sick people and healed them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And He wondered at their unbelief.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24414L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24414L\"></sup>And He was going around the villages teaching.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24415M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24415M\"></sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24415N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24415N\"></sup>He *summoned the twelve and began to send them out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24415O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24415O\"></sup>in pairs, and gave them authority over the unclean spirits;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24416P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24416P\"></sup>and He instructed them that they should take nothing for <i>their</i> journey, except a mere staff—no bread, no bag, no money in their belt—",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but <i>to</i> wear sandals; and <i>He added</i>, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not put on two tunics.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Wherever you enter a house, stay there until you leave town.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Any place that does not receive you or listen to you, as you go out from there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24419Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24419Q\"></sup>shake the dust off the soles of your feet for a testimony against them.”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24420R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24420R\"></sup>They went out and preached that <i>men</i> should repent.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they were casting out many demons and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24421S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24421S\"></sup>were anointing with oil many sick people and healing them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24422T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24422T\"></sup>And King Herod heard <i>of it</i>, for His name had become well known; and <i>people</i> were saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24422U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24422U\"></sup>John the Baptist has risen from the dead, and that is why these miraculous powers are at work in Him.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But others were saying, “He is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24423V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24423V\"></sup>Elijah.” And others were saying, “<i>He is</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24423W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24423W\"></sup>a prophet, like one of the prophets <i>of old</i>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when Herod heard <i>of it</i>, he kept saying, “John, whom I beheaded, has risen!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For Herod himself had sent and had John arrested and bound in prison on account of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24425X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24425X\"></sup>Herodias, the wife of his brother Philip, because he had married her.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For John had been saying to Herod, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24426Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24426Y\"></sup>It is not lawful for you to have your brother’s wife.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24427Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24427Z\"></sup>Herodias had a grudge against him and wanted to put him to death and could not <i>do so</i>;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24428AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24428AA\"></sup>Herod was afraid of John, knowing that he was a righteous and holy man, and he kept him safe. And when he heard him, he was very perplexed; but he used to enjoy listening to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>A strategic day came when Herod on his birthday <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24429AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24429AB\"></sup>gave a banquet for his lords and military commanders and the leading men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24429AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24429AC\"></sup>of Galilee;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and when the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24430AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24430AD\"></sup>Herodias herself came in and danced, she pleased Herod and his dinner guests; and the king said to the girl, “Ask me for whatever you want and I will give it to you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he swore to her, “Whatever you ask of me, I will give it to you; up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24431AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24431AE\"></sup>half of my kingdom.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And she went out and said to her mother, “What shall I ask for?” And she said, “The head of John the Baptist.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Immediately she came in a hurry to the king and asked, saying, “I want you to give me at once the head of John the Baptist on a platter.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And although the king was very sorry, <i>yet</i> because of his oaths and because of his dinner guests, he was unwilling to refuse her.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Immediately the king sent an executioner and commanded <i>him</i> to bring <i>back</i> his head. And he went and had him beheaded in the prison,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and brought his head on a platter, and gave it to the girl; and the girl gave it to her mother.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When his disciples heard <i>about this</i>, they came and took away his body and laid it in a tomb.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24438AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24438AF\"></sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24438AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24438AG\"></sup>apostles *gathered together with Jesus; and they reported to Him all that they had done and taught.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Come away by yourselves to a secluded place and rest a while.”</span> (For there were many <i>people</i> coming and going, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24439AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24439AH\"></sup>they did not even have time to eat.)",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24440AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24440AI\"></sup>They went away in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24440AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24440AJ\"></sup>the boat to a secluded place by themselves.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><i>The people</i> saw them going, and many recognized <i>them</i> and ran there together on foot from all the cities, and got there ahead of them.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Jesus went ashore, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24442AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24442AK\"></sup>saw a large crowd, and He felt compassion for them because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24442AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24442AL\"></sup>they were like sheep without a shepherd; and He began to teach them many things.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When it was already quite late, His disciples came to Him and said, “This place is desolate and it is already quite late;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>send them away so that they may go into the surrounding countryside and villages and buy themselves something to eat.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But He answered them, <span class=\"woj\">“You give them <i>something</i> to eat!”</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24445AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24445AM\"></sup>And they *said to Him, “Shall we go and spend two hundred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24445AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24445AN\"></sup>denarii on bread and give them <i>something</i> to eat?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“How many loaves do you have? Go look!”</span> And when they found out, they *said, “Five, and two fish.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And He commanded them all to sit down by groups on the green grass.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They sat down in groups of hundreds and of fifties.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And He took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up toward heaven, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24449AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24449AO\"></sup>blessed <i>the food</i> and broke the loaves and He kept giving <i>them</i> to the disciples to set before them; and He divided up the two fish among them all.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They all ate and were satisfied,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and they picked up twelve full <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24451AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24451AP\"></sup>baskets of the broken pieces, and also of the fish.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>There were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24452AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24452AQ\"></sup>five thousand men who ate the loaves.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24453AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24453AR\"></sup>Immediately Jesus made His disciples get into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24453AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24453AS\"></sup>the boat and go ahead of <i>Him</i> to the other side to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24453AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24453AT\"></sup>Bethsaida, while He Himself was sending the crowd away.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>After <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24454AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24454AU\"></sup>bidding them farewell, He left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24454AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24454AV\"></sup>for the mountain to pray.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When it was evening, the boat was in the middle of the sea, and He was alone on the land.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Seeing them straining at the oars, for the wind was against them, at about the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24456AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24456AW\"></sup>fourth watch of the night He *came to them, walking on the sea; and He intended to pass by them.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But when they saw Him walking on the sea, they supposed that it was a ghost, and cried out;",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>for they all saw Him and were terrified. But immediately He spoke with them and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24458AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24458AX\"></sup>Take courage; it is I, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24458AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24458AY\"></sup>do not be afraid.”</span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then He got into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24459AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24459AZ\"></sup>the boat with them, and the wind stopped; and they were utterly astonished,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24460BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24460BA\"></sup>they had not gained any insight from the <i>incident of</i> the loaves, but their heart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24460BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24460BB\"></sup>was hardened.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24461BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24461BC\"></sup>When they had crossed over they came to land at Gennesaret, and moored to the shore.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>When they got out of the boat, immediately <i>the people</i> recognized Him,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>and ran about that whole country and began to carry here and there on their pallets those who were sick, to the place they heard He was.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Wherever He entered villages, or cities, or countryside, they were laying the sick in the market places, and imploring Him that they might just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24464BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24464BD\"></sup>touch <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24464BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24464BE\"></sup>the fringe of His cloak; and as many as touched it were being cured."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24465A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24465A\"></sup>The Pharisees and some of the scribes gathered around Him when they had come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24465B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24465B\"></sup>from Jerusalem,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and had seen that some of His disciples were eating their bread with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24466C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24466C\"></sup>impure hands, that is, unwashed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>(For the Pharisees and all the Jews do not eat unless they carefully wash their hands, <i>thus</i> observing the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24467D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24467D\"></sup>traditions of the elders;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <i>when they come</i> from the market place, they do not eat unless they cleanse themselves; and there are many other things which they have received in order to observe, such as the washing of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24468E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24468E\"></sup>cups and pitchers and copper pots.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Pharisees and the scribes *asked Him, “Why do Your disciples not walk according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24469F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24469F\"></sup>tradition of the elders, but eat their bread with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24469G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24469G\"></sup>impure hands?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Rightly did Isaiah prophesy of you hypocrites, as it is written:</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24470H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24470H\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">This people honors Me with their lips</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">But their heart is far away from Me</span>.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24471I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24471I\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">But in vain do they worship Me</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Teaching as doctrines the precepts of men</span>.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Neglecting the commandment of God, you hold to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24472J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24472J\"></sup>tradition of men.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He was also saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You are experts at setting aside the commandment of God in order to keep your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24473K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24473K\"></sup>tradition.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For Moses said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24474L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24474L\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Honor your father and your mother</span>’; and, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24474M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24474M\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">He who speaks evil of father or mother, is to</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">be put to death</span>’;</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but you say, ‘If a man says to <i>his</i> father or <i>his</i> mother, whatever I have that would help you is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24475N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24475N\"></sup>Corban</span> (that is to say, given <i>to God</i>),’",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>you no longer permit him to do anything for <i>his</i> father or <i>his</i> mother;</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><i>thus</i> invalidating the word of God by your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24477O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24477O\"></sup>tradition which you have handed down; and you do many things such as that.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After He called the crowd to Him again, He <i>began</i> saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Listen to Me, all of you, and understand:</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>there is nothing outside the man which can defile him if it goes into him; but the things which proceed out of the man are what defile the man.</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>[<span class=\"woj\">If anyone has ears to hear, let him hear.”</span>]",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he had left the crowd <i>and</i> entered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24481P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24481P\"></sup>the house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24481Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24481Q\"></sup>His disciples questioned Him about the parable.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Are you so lacking in understanding also? Do you not understand that whatever goes into the man from outside cannot defile him,</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>because it does not go into his heart, but into his stomach, and is eliminated?”</span> (<i>Thus He</i> declared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24483R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24483R\"></sup>all foods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24483S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24483S\"></sup>clean.)",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And He was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24484T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24484T\"></sup>That which proceeds out of the man, that is what defiles the man.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed the evil thoughts, fornications, thefts, murders, adulteries,</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>deeds of coveting <i>and</i> wickedness, <i>as well as</i> deceit, sensuality, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24486U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24486U\"></sup>envy, slander, pride <i>and</i> foolishness.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All these evil things proceed from within and defile the man.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24488V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24488V\"></sup>Jesus got up and went away from there to the region of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24488W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24488W\"></sup>Tyre. And when He had entered a house, He wanted no one to know <i>of it</i>; yet He could not escape notice.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But after hearing of Him, a woman whose little daughter had an unclean spirit immediately came and fell at His feet.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the woman was a Gentile, of the Syrophoenician race. And she kept asking Him to cast the demon out of her daughter.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And He was saying to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Let the children be satisfied first, for it is not good to take the children’s bread and throw it to the dogs.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But she answered and *said to Him, “Yes, Lord, <i>but</i> even the dogs under the table feed on the children’s crumbs.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And He said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Because of this answer go; the demon has gone out of your daughter.”</span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And going back to her home, she found the child lying on the bed, the demon having left.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24495X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24495X\"></sup>Again He went out from the region of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24495Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24495Y\"></sup>Tyre, and came through Sidon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24495Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24495Z\"></sup>the Sea of Galilee, within the region of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24495AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24495AA\"></sup>Decapolis.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They *brought to Him one who was deaf and spoke with difficulty, and they *implored Him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24496AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24496AB\"></sup>lay His hand on him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24497AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24497AC\"></sup>Jesus took him aside from the crowd, by himself, and put His fingers into his ears, and after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24497AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24497AD\"></sup>spitting, He touched his tongue <i>with the saliva</i>;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and looking up to heaven with a deep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24498AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24498AE\"></sup>sigh, He *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Ephphatha!”</span> that is, <span class=\"woj\">“Be opened!”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And his ears were opened, and the impediment of his tongue was removed, and he <i>began</i> speaking plainly.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24500AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24500AF\"></sup>He gave them orders not to tell anyone; but the more He ordered them, the more widely they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24500AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24500AG\"></sup>continued to proclaim it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They were utterly astonished, saying, “He has done all things well; He makes even the deaf to hear and the mute to speak.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>In those days, when there was again a large crowd and they had nothing to eat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24502A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24502A\"></sup>Jesus called His disciples and *said to them,",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24503B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24503B\"></sup>I feel compassion for the people because they have remained with Me now three days and have nothing to eat.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If I send them away hungry to their homes, they will faint on the way; and some of them have come from a great distance.”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And His disciples answered Him, “Where will anyone be able <i>to find enough</i> bread here in <i>this</i> desolate place to satisfy these people?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And He was asking them, <span class=\"woj\">“How many loaves do you have?”</span> And they said, “Seven.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And He *directed the people to sit down on the ground; and taking the seven loaves, He gave thanks and broke them, and started giving them to His disciples to serve to them, and they served them to the people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They also had a few small fish; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24508C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24508C\"></sup>after He had blessed them, He ordered these to be served as well.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they ate and were satisfied; and they picked up seven large <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24509D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24509D\"></sup>baskets full of what was left over of the broken pieces.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>About four thousand were <i>there</i>; and He sent them away.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And immediately He entered the boat with His disciples and came to the district of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24511E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24511E\"></sup>Dalmanutha.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24512F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24512F\"></sup>The Pharisees came out and began to argue with Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24512G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24512G\"></sup>seeking from Him a sign from heaven, to test Him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24513H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24513H\"></sup>Sighing deeply in His spirit, He *said, <span class=\"woj\">“Why does this generation seek for a sign? Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24513I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24513I\"></sup>no sign will be given to this generation.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Leaving them, He again embarked and went away to the other side.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they had forgotten to take bread, and did not have more than one loaf in the boat with them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And He was giving orders to them, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24516J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24516J\"></sup>Watch out! Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and the leaven of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24516K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24516K\"></sup>Herod.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They <i>began</i> to discuss with one another <i>the fact</i> that they had no bread.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Jesus, aware of this, *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why do you discuss <i>the fact</i> that you have no bread? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24518L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24518L\"></sup>Do you not yet see or understand? Do you have a hardened heart?</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24519M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24519M\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Having eyes, do you not see</span>? <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And having ears, do you not hear</span>? And do you not remember,</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>when I broke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24520N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24520N\"></sup>the five loaves for the five thousand, how many <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24520O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24520O\"></sup>baskets full of broken pieces you picked up?”</span> They *said to Him, “Twelve.”",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When <i>I broke</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24521P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24521P\"></sup>the seven for the four thousand, how many large <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24521Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24521Q\"></sup>baskets full of broken pieces did you pick up?”</span> And they *said to Him, “Seven.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24522R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24522R\"></sup>Do you not yet understand?”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they *came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24523S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24523S\"></sup>Bethsaida. And they *brought a blind man to Jesus and *implored Him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24523T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24523T\"></sup>touch him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Taking the blind man by the hand, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24524U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24524U\"></sup>brought him out of the village; and after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24524V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24524V\"></sup>spitting on his eyes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24524W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24524W\"></sup>laying His hands on him, He asked him, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you see anything?”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he looked up and said, “I see men, for I see <i>them</i> like trees, walking around.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then again He laid His hands on his eyes; and he looked intently and was restored, and <i>began</i> to see everything clearly.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And He sent him to his home, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not even enter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24527X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24527X\"></sup>the village.”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24528Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24528Y\"></sup>Jesus went out, along with His disciples, to the villages of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24528Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24528Z\"></sup>Caesarea Philippi; and on the way He questioned His disciples, saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Who do people say that I am?”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24529AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24529AA\"></sup>They told Him, saying, “John the Baptist; and others <i>say</i> Elijah; but others, one of the prophets.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And He <i>continued</i> by questioning them, <span class=\"woj\">“But who do you say that I am?”</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24530AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24530AB\"></sup>Peter *answered and *said to Him, “You are the Christ.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24531AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24531AC\"></sup>He warned them to tell no one about Him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24532AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24532AD\"></sup>And He began to teach them that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24532AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24532AE\"></sup>the Son of Man must suffer many things and be rejected by the elders and the chief priests and the scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And He was stating the matter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24533AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24533AF\"></sup>plainly. And Peter took Him aside and began to rebuke Him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But turning around and seeing His disciples, He rebuked Peter and *said, <span class=\"woj\">“Get behind Me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24534AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24534AG\"></sup>Satan; for you are not setting your mind on God’s interests, but man’s.”</span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And He summoned the crowd with His disciples, and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“If anyone wishes to come after Me, he must deny himself, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24535AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24535AH\"></sup>take up his cross and follow Me.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24536AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24536AI\"></sup>whoever wishes to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life for My sake and the gospel’s will save it.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>For what does it profit a man to gain the whole world, and forfeit his soul?</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For what will a man give in exchange for his soul?</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24539AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24539AJ\"></sup>whoever is ashamed of Me and My words in this adulterous and sinful generation, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24539AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24539AK\"></sup>the Son of Man will also be ashamed of him when He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24539AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24539AL\"></sup>comes in the glory of His Father with the holy angels.”</span>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>And Jesus was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24540A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24540A\"></sup>Truly I say to you, there are some of those who are standing here who will not taste death until they see the kingdom of God after it has come with power.”</span>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24541B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24541B\"></sup>Six days later, Jesus *took with Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24541C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24541C\"></sup>Peter and James and John, and *brought them up on a high mountain by themselves. And He was transfigured before them;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24542D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24542D\"></sup>His garments became radiant and exceedingly white, as no launderer on earth can whiten them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Elijah appeared to them along with Moses; and they were talking with Jesus.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Peter *said to Jesus, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24544E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24544E\"></sup>Rabbi, it is good for us to be here; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24544F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24544F\"></sup>let us make three tabernacles, one for You, and one for Moses, and one for Elijah.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For he did not know what to answer; for they became terrified.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then a cloud formed, overshadowing them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24546G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24546G\"></sup>a voice came out of the cloud, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24546H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24546H\"></sup>This is My beloved Son, listen to Him!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All at once they looked around and saw no one with them anymore, except Jesus alone.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24548I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24548I\"></sup>As they were coming down from the mountain, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24548J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24548J\"></sup>gave them orders not to relate to anyone what they had seen, until the Son of Man rose from the dead.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They seized upon that statement, discussing with one another what rising from the dead meant.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They asked Him, saying, “<i>Why is it</i> that the scribes say that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24550K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24550K\"></sup>Elijah must come first?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Elijah does first come and restore all things. And <i>yet</i> how is it written of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24551L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24551L\"></sup>the Son of Man that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24551M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24551M\"></sup>He will suffer many things and be treated with contempt?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But I say to you that Elijah has indeed come, and they did to him whatever they wished, just as it is written of him.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24553N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24553N\"></sup>When they came <i>back</i> to the disciples, they saw a large crowd around them, and <i>some</i> scribes arguing with them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Immediately, when the entire crowd saw Him, they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24554O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24554O\"></sup>amazed and <i>began</i> running up to greet Him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And He asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“What are you discussing with them?”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And one of the crowd answered Him, “Teacher, I brought You my son, possessed with a spirit which makes him mute;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and whenever it seizes him, it slams him <i>to the ground</i> and he foams <i>at the mouth</i>, and grinds his teeth and stiffens out. I told Your disciples to cast it out, and they could not <i>do it</i>.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And He *answered them and *said, <span class=\"woj\">“O unbelieving generation, how long shall I be with you? How long shall I put up with you? Bring him to Me!”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They brought the boy to Him. When he saw Him, immediately the spirit threw him into a convulsion, and falling to the ground, he <i>began</i> rolling around and foaming <i>at the mouth</i>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And He asked his father, <span class=\"woj\">“How long has this been happening to him?”</span> And he said, “From childhood.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>It has often thrown him both into the fire and into the water to destroy him. But if You can do anything, take pity on us and help us!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“‘If You can?’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24562P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24562P\"></sup>All things are possible to him who believes.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Immediately the boy’s father cried out and said, “I do believe; help my unbelief.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Jesus saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24564Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24564Q\"></sup>a crowd was rapidly gathering, He rebuked the unclean spirit, saying to it, <span class=\"woj\">“You deaf and mute spirit, I command you, come out of him and do not enter him again.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>After crying out and throwing him into terrible convulsions, it came out; and <i>the boy</i> became so much like a corpse that most <i>of them</i> said, “He is dead!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Jesus took him by the hand and raised him; and he got up.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When He came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24567R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24567R\"></sup>into <i>the</i> house, His disciples <i>began</i> questioning Him privately, “Why could we not drive it out?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“This kind cannot come out by anything but prayer.”</span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24569S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24569S\"></sup>From there they went out and <i>began</i> to go through Galilee, and He did not want anyone to know <i>about it</i>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For He was teaching His disciples and telling them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24570T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24570T\"></sup>The Son of Man is to be delivered into the hands of men, and they will kill Him; and when He has been killed, He will rise three days later.”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24571U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24571U\"></sup>they did not understand <i>this</i> statement, and they were afraid to ask Him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24572V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24572V\"></sup>They came to Capernaum; and when He was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24572W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24572W\"></sup>the house, He <i>began</i> to question them, <span class=\"woj\">“What were you discussing on the way?”</span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But they kept silent, for on the way <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24573X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24573X\"></sup>they had discussed with one another which <i>of them was</i> the greatest.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Sitting down, He called the twelve and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24574Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24574Y\"></sup>If anyone wants to be first, he shall be last of all and servant of all.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Taking a child, He set him before them, and taking him in His arms, He said to them,",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24576Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24576Z\"></sup>Whoever receives one child like this in My name receives Me; and whoever receives Me does not receive Me, but Him who sent Me.”</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24577AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24577AA\"></sup>John said to Him, “Teacher, we saw someone casting out demons in Your name, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24577AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24577AB\"></sup>we tried to prevent him because he was not following us.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not hinder him, for there is no one who will perform a miracle in My name, and be able soon afterward to speak evil of Me.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24579AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24579AC\"></sup>For he who is not against us is for us.</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24580AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24580AD\"></sup>whoever gives you a cup of water to drink because of your name as <i>followers</i> of Christ, truly I say to you, he will not lose his reward.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24581AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24581AE\"></sup>Whoever causes one of these little ones who believe to stumble, it would be better for him if, with a heavy millstone hung around his neck, he had been cast into the sea.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24582AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24582AF\"></sup>If your hand causes you to stumble, cut it off; it is better for you to enter life crippled, than, having your two hands, to go into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24582AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24582AG\"></sup>hell, into the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24582AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24582AH\"></sup>unquenchable fire,</span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>[<span class=\"woj\">where <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">their worm does not die, and the fire is not quenched</span>.</span>]",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>If your foot causes you to stumble, cut it off; it is better for you to enter life lame, than, having your two feet, to be cast into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24584AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24584AI\"></sup>hell,</span>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>[<span class=\"woj\">where <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">their worm does not die, and the fire is not quenched</span>.</span>]",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24586AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24586AJ\"></sup>If your eye causes you to stumble, throw it out; it is better for you to enter the kingdom of God with one eye, than, having two eyes, to be cast into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24586AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24586AK\"></sup>hell,</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24587AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24587AL\"></sup>where <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">their worm does not die, and</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24587AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24587AM\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the fire is not quenched</span>.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“For everyone will be salted with fire.</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Salt is good; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24589AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24589AN\"></sup>if the salt becomes unsalty, with what will you make it salty <i>again</i>? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24589AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24589AO\"></sup>Have salt in yourselves, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24589AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24589AP\"></sup>be at peace with one another.”</span>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24590A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24590A\"></sup>Getting up, He *went from there to the region of Judea and beyond the Jordan; crowds *gathered around Him again, and, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24590B\"></sup>according to His custom, He once more <i>began</i> to teach them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><i>Some</i> Pharisees came up to Jesus, testing Him, and <i>began</i> to question Him whether it was lawful for a man to divorce a wife.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And He answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“What did Moses command you?”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24593C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24593C\"></sup>Moses permitted <i>a man</i> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">to write a certificate of divorce and</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">send</span> <i>her</i> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">away</span>.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24594D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24594D\"></sup>Because of your hardness of heart he wrote you this commandment.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24595E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24595E\"></sup>from the beginning of creation, <i>God</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24595F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24595F\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">made them male and female</span>.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24596G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24596G\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother</span>,</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24597H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24597H\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and the two shall become one flesh</span>; so they are no longer two, but one flesh.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What therefore God has joined together, let no man separate.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the house the disciples <i>began</i> questioning Him about this again.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24600I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24600I\"></sup>Whoever divorces his wife and marries another woman commits adultery against her;</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24601J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24601J\"></sup>if she herself divorces her husband and marries another man, she is committing adultery.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24602K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24602K\"></sup>And they were bringing children to Him so that He might touch them; but the disciples rebuked them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But when Jesus saw this, He was indignant and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Permit the children to come to Me; do not hinder them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24603L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24603L\"></sup>for the kingdom of God belongs to such as these.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24604M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24604M\"></sup>whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child will not enter it <i>at all</i>.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24605N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24605N\"></sup>took them in His arms and <i>began</i> blessing them, laying His hands on them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24606O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24606O\"></sup>As He was setting out on a journey, a man ran up to Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24606P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24606P\"></sup>knelt before Him, and asked Him, “Good Teacher, what shall I do to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24606Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24606Q\"></sup>inherit eternal life?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Why do you call Me good? No one is good except God alone.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You know the commandments, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24608R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24608R\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Do not murder, Do not commit adultery, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness</span>, Do not defraud, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Honor your father and mother</span>.’”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he said to Him, “Teacher, I have kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24609S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24609S\"></sup>all these things from my youth up.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Looking at him, Jesus felt a love for him and said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“One thing you lack: go and sell all you possess and give to the poor, and you will have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24610T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24610T\"></sup>treasure in heaven; and come, follow Me.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But at these words he was saddened, and he went away grieving, for he was one who owned much property.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Jesus, looking around, *said to His disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24612U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24612U\"></sup>How hard it will be for those who are wealthy to enter the kingdom of God!”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The disciples <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24613V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24613V\"></sup>were amazed at His words. But Jesus *answered again and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Children, how hard it is to enter the kingdom of God!</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24614W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24614W\"></sup>It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They were even more astonished and said to Him, “Then who can be saved?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Looking at them, Jesus *said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24616X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24616X\"></sup>With people it is impossible, but not with God; for all things are possible with God.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24617Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24617Y\"></sup>Peter began to say to Him, “Behold, we have left everything and followed You.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24618Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24618Z\"></sup>there is no one who has left house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children or farms, for My sake and for the gospel’s sake,</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but that he will receive a hundred times as much now in the present age, houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and farms, along with persecutions; and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24619AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24619AA\"></sup>the age to come, eternal life.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24620AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24620AB\"></sup>many <i>who are</i> first will be last, and the last, first.”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24621AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24621AC\"></sup>They were on the road going up to Jerusalem, and Jesus was walking on ahead of them; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24621AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24621AD\"></sup>were amazed, and those who followed were fearful. And again He took the twelve aside and began to tell them what was going to happen to Him,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><i>saying</i>, <span class=\"woj\">“Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24622AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24622AE\"></sup>the Son of Man will be delivered to the chief priests and the scribes; and they will condemn Him to death and will hand Him over to the Gentiles.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>They will mock Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24623AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24623AF\"></sup>spit on Him, and scourge Him and kill <i>Him</i>, and three days later He will rise again.”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24624AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24624AG\"></sup>James and John, the two sons of Zebedee, *came up to Jesus, saying, “Teacher, we want You to do for us whatever we ask of You.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“What do you want Me to do for you?”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They said to Him, “Grant that we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24626AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24626AH\"></sup>may sit, one on Your right and one on <i>Your</i> left, in Your glory.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You do not know what you are asking. Are you able <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24627AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24627AI\"></sup>to drink the cup that I drink, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24627AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24627AJ\"></sup>to be baptized with the baptism with which I am baptized?”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They said to Him, “We are able.” And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The cup that I drink <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24628AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24628AK\"></sup>you shall drink; and you shall be baptized with the baptism with which I am baptized.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But to sit on My right or on <i>My</i> left, this is not Mine to give; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24629AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24629AL\"></sup>but it is for those for whom it has been prepared.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24630AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24630AM\"></sup>Hearing <i>this</i>, the ten began to feel indignant with James and John.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Calling them to Himself, Jesus *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You know that those who are recognized as rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them; and their great men exercise authority over them.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But it is not this way among you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24632AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24632AN\"></sup>but whoever wishes to become great among you shall be your servant;</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and whoever wishes to be first among you shall be slave of all.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>For even the Son of Man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24634AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24634AO\"></sup>did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give His life a ransom for many.”</span>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24635AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24635AP\"></sup>Then they *came to Jericho. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24635AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24635AQ\"></sup>as He was leaving Jericho with His disciples and a large crowd, a blind beggar <i>named</i> Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, was sitting by the road.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When he heard that it was Jesus the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24636AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24636AR\"></sup>Nazarene, he began to cry out and say, “Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24636AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24636AS\"></sup>Son of David, have mercy on me!”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Many were sternly telling him to be quiet, but he kept crying out all the more, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24637AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24637AT\"></sup>Son of David, have mercy on me!”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And Jesus stopped and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Call him <i>here</i>.”</span> So they *called the blind man, saying to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24638AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24638AU\"></sup>Take courage, stand up! He is calling for you.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Throwing aside his cloak, he jumped up and came to Jesus.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And answering him, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“What do you want Me to do for you?”</span> And the blind man said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24640AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24640AV\"></sup>Rabboni, <i>I want</i> to regain my sight!”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Go; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24641AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24641AW\"></sup>your faith has made you well.”</span> Immediately he regained his sight and <i>began</i> following Him on the road."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24642A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24642A\"></sup>As they *approached Jerusalem, at Bethphage and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24642B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24642B\"></sup>Bethany, near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24642C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24642C\"></sup>the Mount of Olives, He *sent two of His disciples,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Go into the village opposite you, and immediately as you enter it, you will find a colt tied <i>there</i>, on which no one yet has ever sat; untie it and bring it <i>here</i>.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If anyone says to you, ‘Why are you doing this?’ you say, ‘The Lord has need of it’; and immediately he will send it back here.”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They went away and found a colt tied at the door, outside in the street; and they *untied it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Some of the bystanders were saying to them, “What are you doing, untying the colt?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They spoke to them just as Jesus had told <i>them</i>, and they gave them permission.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24648D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24648D\"></sup>They *brought the colt to Jesus and put their coats on it; and He sat on it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And many spread their coats in the road, and others <i>spread</i> leafy branches which they had cut from the fields.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Those who went in front and those who followed were shouting:“Hosanna!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24650E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24650E\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord</span>;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Blessed <i>is</i> the coming kingdom of our father David;Hosanna <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24651F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24651F\"></sup>in the highest!”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24652G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24652G\"></sup>Jesus entered Jerusalem <i>and came</i> into the temple; and after looking around at everything, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24652H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24652H\"></sup>He left for Bethany with the twelve, since it was already late.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24653I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24653I\"></sup>On the next day, when they had left Bethany, He became hungry.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Seeing at a distance a fig tree in leaf, He went <i>to see</i> if perhaps He would find anything on it; and when He came to it, He found nothing but leaves, for it was not the season for figs.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said to it, <span class=\"woj\">“May no one ever eat fruit from you again!”</span> And His disciples were listening.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24656J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24656J\"></sup>Then they *came to Jerusalem. And He entered the temple and began to drive out those who were buying and selling in the temple, and overturned the tables of the money changers and the seats of those who were selling doves;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and He would not permit anyone to carry merchandise through the temple.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And He <i>began</i> to teach and say to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Is it not written, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24658K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24658K\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">My house shall be called a house of prayer for all the nations</span>’? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24658L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24658L\"></sup>But you have made it a <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">robbers</span>’ <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">den</span>.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The chief priests and the scribes heard <i>this</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24659M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24659M\"></sup><i>began</i> seeking how to destroy Him; for they were afraid of Him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24659N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24659N\"></sup>the whole crowd was astonished at His teaching.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24660O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24660O\"></sup>When evening came, they would go out of the city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24661P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24661P\"></sup>As they were passing by in the morning, they saw the fig tree withered from the roots <i>up</i>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Being reminded, Peter *said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24662Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24662Q\"></sup>Rabbi, look, the fig tree which You cursed has withered.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Jesus *answered saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24663R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24663R\"></sup>Have faith in God.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24664S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24664S\"></sup>Truly I say to you, whoever says to this mountain, ‘Be taken up and cast into the sea,’ and does not doubt in his heart, but believes that what he says is going to happen, it will be <i>granted</i> him.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Therefore I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24665T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24665T\"></sup>all things for which you pray and ask, believe that you have received them, and they will be <i>granted</i> you.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Whenever you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24666U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24666U\"></sup>stand praying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24666V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24666V\"></sup>forgive, if you have anything against anyone, so that your Father who is in heaven will also forgive you your transgressions.</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>[<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24667W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24667W\"></sup>But if you do not forgive, neither will your Father who is in heaven forgive your transgressions.”</span>]",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They *came again to Jerusalem. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24668X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24668X\"></sup>And as He was walking in the temple, the chief priests and the scribes and the elders *came to Him,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <i>began</i> saying to Him, “By what authority are You doing these things, or who gave You this authority to do these things?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I will ask you one question, and you answer Me, and <i>then</i> I will tell you by what authority I do these things.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Was the baptism of John from heaven, or from men? Answer Me.”</span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They <i>began</i> reasoning among themselves, saying, “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ He will say, ‘Then why did you not believe him?’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But shall we say, ‘From men’?”—they were afraid of the people, for everyone considered John to have been a real prophet.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Answering Jesus, they *said, “We do not know.” And Jesus *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Nor will I tell you by what authority I do these things.”</span>"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24675A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24675A\"></sup>And He began to speak to them in parables: <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24675B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24675B\"></sup>A man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24675C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24675C\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">planted a vineyard and put a</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">wall around it, and dug a vat under the wine press and built a tower</span>, and rented it out to vine-growers and went on a journey.</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At the <i>harvest</i> time he sent a slave to the vine-growers, in order to receive <i>some</i> of the produce of the vineyard from the vine-growers.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They took him, and beat him and sent him away empty-handed.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Again he sent them another slave, and they wounded him in the head, and treated him shamefully.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he sent another, and that one they killed; and <i>so with</i> many others, beating some and killing others.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He had one more <i>to send</i>, a beloved son; he sent him last <i>of all</i> to them, saying, ‘They will respect my son.’</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But those vine-growers said to one another, ‘This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours!’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They took him, and killed him and threw him out of the vineyard.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What will the owner of the vineyard do? He will come and destroy the vine-growers, and will give the vineyard to others.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Have you not even read this Scripture:</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24684D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24684D\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The stone which the builders rejected</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">This became the chief corner</span> <i>stone</i>;</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24685E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24685E\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">This came about from the Lord</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And it is marvelous in our eyes</span>’?”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24686F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24686F\"></sup>And they were seeking to seize Him, and <i>yet</i> they feared the people, for they understood that He spoke the parable against them. And <i>so</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24686G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24686G\"></sup>they left Him and went away.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24687H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24687H\"></sup>Then they *sent some of the Pharisees and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24687I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24687I\"></sup>Herodians to Him in order to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24687J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24687J\"></sup>trap Him in a statement.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They *came and *said to Him, “Teacher, we know that You are truthful and defer to no one; for You are not partial to any, but teach the way of God in truth. Is it lawful to pay a poll-tax to Caesar, or not?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Shall we pay or shall we not pay?” But He, knowing their hypocrisy, said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you testing Me? Bring Me a denarius to look at.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They brought <i>one</i>. And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Whose likeness and inscription is this?”</span> And they said to Him, “Caesar’s.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24691K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24691K\"></sup>Render to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”</span> And they were amazed at Him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24692L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24692L\"></sup><i>Some</i> Sadducees (who say that there is no resurrection) *came to Jesus, and <i>began</i> questioning Him, saying,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Teacher, Moses wrote for us that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24693M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24693M\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">if a man’s brother dies</span> and leaves behind a wife <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and leaves no child, his brother should</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">marry the wife and raise up children to his brother</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There were seven brothers; and the first took a wife, and died leaving no children.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The second one married her, and died leaving behind no children; and the third likewise;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and <i>so</i> all seven left no children. Last of all the woman died also.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the resurrection, when they rise again, which one’s wife will she be? For all seven had married her.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Is this not the reason you are mistaken, that you do not understand the Scriptures or the power of God?</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For when they rise from the dead, they neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But regarding the fact that the dead rise again, have you not read in the book of Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24700N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24700N\"></sup>in the <i>passage</i> about <i>the burning</i> bush, how God spoke to him, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24700O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24700O\"></sup>I <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob</span>’?</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24701P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24701P\"></sup>He is not the God of the dead, but of the living; you are greatly mistaken.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24702Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24702Q\"></sup>One of the scribes came and heard them arguing, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24702R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24702R\"></sup>recognizing that He had answered them well, asked Him, “What commandment is the foremost of all?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“The foremost is, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24703S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24703S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Hear</span>, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Israel! The Lord our God is one Lord</span>;</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24704T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24704T\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and you shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind, and with all your strength</span>.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The second is this, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24705U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24705U\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">You shall love your neighbor as yourself</span>.’ There is no other commandment greater than these.”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The scribe said to Him, “Right, Teacher; You have truly stated that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24706V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24706V\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">He is One, and there is no one else besides Him</span>;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24707W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24707W\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and to love Him with all the heart and with all the understanding and with all the strength, and to love one’s neighbor as himself</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24707X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24707X\"></sup>is much more than all burnt offerings and sacrifices.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Jesus saw that he had answered intelligently, He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“You are not far from the kingdom of God.”</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24708Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24708Y\"></sup>After that, no one would venture to ask Him any more questions.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24709Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24709Z\"></sup>And Jesus <i>began</i> to say, as He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24709AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24709AA\"></sup>taught in the temple, <span class=\"woj\">“How <i>is it that</i> the scribes say that the Christ is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24709AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24709AB\"></sup>son of David?</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>David himself said in the Holy Spirit,</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24710AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24710AC\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The Lord said to my Lord</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\">“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Sit at My right hand</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Until I put Your enemies beneath Your feet</span>.”’</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>David himself calls Him ‘Lord’; so in what sense is He his son?”</span> And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24711AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24711AD\"></sup>the large crowd enjoyed listening to Him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24712AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24712AE\"></sup>In His teaching He was saying: <span class=\"woj\">“Beware of the scribes who like to walk around in long robes, and <i>like</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24712AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24712AF\"></sup>respectful greetings in the market places,</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and chief seats in the synagogues and places of honor at banquets,</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24714AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24714AG\"></sup>who devour widows’ houses, and for appearance’s sake offer long prayers; these will receive greater condemnation.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24715AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24715AH\"></sup>And He sat down opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24715AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24715AI\"></sup>the treasury, and <i>began</i> observing how the people were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24715AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24715AJ\"></sup>putting money into the treasury; and many rich people were putting in large sums.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>A poor widow came and put in two small copper coins, which amount to a cent.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Calling His disciples to Him, He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, this poor widow put in more than all the contributors to the treasury;</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>for they all put in out of their surplus, but she, out of her poverty, put in all she owned, all she had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24718AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24718AK\"></sup>to live on.”</span>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24719A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24719A\"></sup>As He was going out of the temple, one of His disciples *said to Him, “Teacher, behold what wonderful stones and what wonderful buildings!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you see these great buildings? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24720B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24720B\"></sup>Not one stone will be left upon another which will not be torn down.”</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As He was sitting on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24721C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24721C\"></sup>the Mount of Olives opposite the temple, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24721D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24721D\"></sup>Peter and James and John and Andrew were questioning Him privately,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Tell us, when will these things be, and what <i>will be</i> the sign when all these things are going to be fulfilled?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Jesus began to say to them, <span class=\"woj\">“See to it that no one misleads you.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Many will come in My name, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24724E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24724E\"></sup>I am <i>He</i>!’ and will mislead many.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When you hear of wars and rumors of wars, do not be frightened; <i>those things</i> must take place; but <i>that is</i> not yet the end.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For nation will rise up against nation, and kingdom against kingdom; there will be earthquakes in various places; there will <i>also</i> be famines. These things are <i>merely</i> the beginning of birth pangs.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“But be on your guard; for they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24727F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24727F\"></sup>deliver you to <i>the</i> courts, and you will be flogged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24727G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24727G\"></sup>in <i>the</i> synagogues, and you will stand before governors and kings for My sake, as a testimony to them.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24728H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24728H\"></sup>The gospel must first be preached to all the nations.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24729I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24729I\"></sup>When they arrest you and hand you over, do not worry beforehand about what you are to say, but say whatever is given you in that hour; for it is not you who speak, but <i>it is</i> the Holy Spirit.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Brother will betray brother to death, and a father <i>his</i> child; and children will rise up against parents and have them put to death.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24731J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24731J\"></sup>You will be hated by all because of My name, but the one who endures to the end, he will be saved.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24732K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24732K\"></sup>when you see the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24732L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24732L\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">abomination of desolation</span> standing where it should not be</span> (let the reader understand), <span class=\"woj\">then those who are in Judea must flee to the mountains.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24733M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24733M\"></sup>The one who is on the housetop must not go down, or go in to get anything out of his house;</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and the one who is in the field must not turn back to get his coat.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing babies in those days!</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But pray that it may not happen in the winter.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For those days will be a <i>time of</i> tribulation such as has not occurred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24737N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24737N\"></sup>since the beginning of the creation which God created until now, and never will.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Unless the Lord had shortened <i>those</i> days, no life would have been saved; but for the sake of the elect, whom He chose, He shortened the days.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And then if anyone says to you, ‘Behold, here is the Christ’; or, ‘Behold, <i>He is</i> there’; do not believe <i>him</i>;</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for false Christs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24740O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24740O\"></sup>false prophets will arise, and will show <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24740P\"></sup>signs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24740Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24740Q\"></sup>wonders, in order to lead astray, if possible, the elect.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But take heed; behold, I have told you everything in advance.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“But in those days, after that tribulation, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24742R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24742R\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the sun will be darkened and the moon will not give its light</span>,</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24743S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24743S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and the stars will be falling</span> from heaven, and the powers that are in the heavens will be shaken.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then they will see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24744T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24744T\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the Son of Man</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24744U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24744U\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">coming in clouds</span> with great power and glory.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And then He will send forth the angels, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24745V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24745V\"></sup>will gather together His elect from the four winds, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24745W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24745W\"></sup>from the farthest end of the earth to the farthest end of heaven.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Now learn the parable from the fig tree: when its branch has already become tender and puts forth its leaves, you know that summer is near.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Even so, you too, when you see these things happening, recognize that He is near, <i>right</i> at the door.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Truly I say to you, this generation will not pass away until all these things take place.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Heaven and earth will pass away, but My words will not pass away.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24750X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24750X\"></sup>But of that day or hour no one knows, not even the angels in heaven, nor the Son, but the Father <i>alone</i>.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Take heed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24751Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24751Y\"></sup>keep on the alert; for you do not know when the <i>appointed</i> time will come.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24752Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24752Z\"></sup><i>It is</i> like a man away on a journey, <i>who</i> upon leaving his house and putting his slaves in charge, <i>assigning</i> to each one his task, also commanded the doorkeeper to stay on the alert.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24753AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24753AA\"></sup>be on the alert—for you do not know when the master of the house is coming, whether in the evening, at midnight, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24753AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24753AB\"></sup>when the rooster crows, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24753AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24753AC\"></sup>in the morning—</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>in case he should come suddenly and find you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24754AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24754AD\"></sup>asleep.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>What I say to you I say to all, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24755AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24755AE\"></sup>Be on the alert!’”</span>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24756A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24756A\"></sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24756B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24756B\"></sup>the Passover and Unleavened Bread were two days away; and the chief priests and the scribes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24756C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24756C\"></sup>were seeking how to seize Him by stealth and kill <i>Him</i>;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>for they were saying, “Not during the festival, otherwise there might be a riot of the people.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24758D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24758D\"></sup>While He was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24758E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24758E\"></sup>Bethany at the home of Simon the leper, and reclining <i>at the table</i>, there came a woman with an alabaster vial of very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24758F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24758F\"></sup>costly perfume of pure nard; <i>and</i> she broke the vial and poured it over His head.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But some were indignantly <i>remarking</i> to one another, “Why has this perfume been wasted?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For this perfume might have been sold for over three hundred denarii, and <i>the money</i> given to the poor.” And they were scolding her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Let her alone; why do you bother her? She has done a good deed to Me.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For you always have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24762G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24762G\"></sup>the poor with you, and whenever you wish you can do good to them; but you do not always have Me.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>She has done what she could; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24763H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24763H\"></sup>she has anointed My body beforehand for the burial.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24764I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24764I\"></sup>wherever the gospel is preached in the whole world, what this woman has done will also be spoken of in memory of her.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24765J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24765J\"></sup>Then Judas Iscariot, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24765K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24765K\"></sup>who was one of the twelve, went off to the chief priests in order to betray Him to them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They were glad when they heard <i>this</i>, and promised to give him money. And he <i>began</i> seeking how to betray Him at an opportune time.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24767L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24767L\"></sup>On the first day of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24767M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24767M\"></sup>Unleavened Bread, when the Passover <i>lamb</i> was being <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24767N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24767N\"></sup>sacrificed, His disciples *said to Him, “Where do You want us to go and prepare for You to eat the Passover?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He *sent two of His disciples and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Go into the city, and a man will meet you carrying a pitcher of water; follow him;</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and wherever he enters, say to the owner of the house, ‘The Teacher says, “Where is My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24769O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24769O\"></sup>guest room in which I may eat the Passover with My disciples?”’</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he himself will show you a large upper room furnished <i>and</i> ready; prepare for us there.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The disciples went out and came to the city, and found <i>it</i> just as He had told them; and they prepared the Passover.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24772P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24772P\"></sup>When it was evening He *came with the twelve.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As they were reclining <i>at the table</i> and eating, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you that one of you will betray Me—one who is eating with Me.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They began to be grieved and to say to Him one by one, “Surely not I?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<i>It is</i> one of the twelve, one who dips with Me in the bowl.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For the Son of Man <i>is to</i> go just as it is written of Him; but woe to that man by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! <i>It would have been</i> good for that man if he had not been born.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24777Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24777Q\"></sup>While they were eating, He took <i>some</i> bread, and after a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24777R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24777R\"></sup>blessing He broke <i>it</i>, and gave <i>it</i> to them, and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Take <i>it</i>; this is My body.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And when He had taken a cup <i>and</i> given thanks, He gave <i>it</i> to them, and they all drank from it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“This is My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24779S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24779S\"></sup>blood of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24779T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24779T\"></sup>covenant, which is poured out for many.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Truly I say to you, I will never again drink of the fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new in the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24781U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24781U\"></sup>After singing a hymn, they went out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24781V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24781V\"></sup>the Mount of Olives.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24782W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24782W\"></sup>And Jesus *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You will all fall away, because it is written, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24782X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24782X\"></sup>I <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">will strike down the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered</span>.’</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But after I have been raised, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24783Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24783Y\"></sup>I will go ahead of you to Galilee.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But Peter said to Him, “<i>Even</i> though all may fall away, yet I will not.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Jesus *said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24785Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24785Z\"></sup>this very night, before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24785AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24785AA\"></sup>a rooster crows twice, you yourself will deny Me three times.”</span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But <i>Peter</i> kept saying insistently, “<i>Even</i> if I have to die with You, I will not deny You!” And they all were saying the same thing also.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24787AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24787AB\"></sup>They *came to a place named Gethsemane; and He *said to His disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Sit here until I have prayed.”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And He *took with Him Peter and James and John, and began to be very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24788AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24788AC\"></sup>distressed and troubled.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And He *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24789AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24789AD\"></sup>My soul is deeply grieved to the point of death; remain here and keep watch.”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And He went a little beyond <i>them</i>, and fell to the ground and <i>began</i> to pray that if it were possible, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24790AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24790AE\"></sup>the hour might pass Him by.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And He was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24791AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24791AF\"></sup>Abba! Father! All things are possible for You; remove this cup from Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24791AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24791AG\"></sup>yet not what I will, but what You will.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And He *came and *found them sleeping, and *said to Peter, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon, are you asleep? Could you not keep watch for one hour?</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24793AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24793AH\"></sup>Keep watching and praying that you may not come into temptation; the spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Again He went away and prayed, saying the same words.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And again He came and found them sleeping, for their eyes were very heavy; and they did not know what to answer Him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And He *came the third time, and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Are you still sleeping and resting? It is enough; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24796AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24796AI\"></sup>the hour has come; behold, the Son of Man is being betrayed into the hands of sinners.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Get up, let us be going; behold, the one who betrays Me is at hand!”</span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24798AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24798AJ\"></sup>Immediately while He was still speaking, Judas, one of the twelve, *came up accompanied by a crowd with swords and clubs, <i>who were</i> from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Now he who was betraying Him had given them a signal, saying, “Whomever I kiss, He is the one; seize Him and lead Him away under guard.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>After coming, Judas immediately went to Him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24800AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24800AK\"></sup>Rabbi!” and kissed Him.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>They laid hands on Him and seized Him.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But one of those who stood by drew his sword, and struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his ear.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Have you come out with swords and clubs to arrest Me, as <i>you would</i> against a robber?</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Every day I was with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24804AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24804AL\"></sup>in the temple teaching, and you did not seize Me; but <i>this has taken place</i> to fulfill the Scriptures.”</span>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And they all left Him and fled.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>A young man was following Him, wearing <i>nothing but</i> a linen sheet over <i>his</i> naked <i>body</i>; and they *seized him.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>But he pulled free of the linen sheet and escaped naked.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24808AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24808AM\"></sup>They led Jesus away to the high priest; and all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes *gathered together.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Peter had followed Him at a distance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24809AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24809AN\"></sup>right into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24809AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24809AO\"></sup>the courtyard of the high priest; and he was sitting with the officers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24809AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24809AP\"></sup>warming himself at the fire.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Now the chief priests and the whole <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24810AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24810AQ\"></sup>Council kept trying to obtain testimony against Jesus to put Him to death, and they were not finding any.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>For many were giving false testimony against Him, but their testimony was not consistent.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Some stood up and <i>began</i> to give false testimony against Him, saying,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>“We heard Him say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24813AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24813AR\"></sup>I will destroy this temple made with hands, and in three days I will build another made without hands.’”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Not even in this respect was their testimony consistent.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>The high priest stood up <i>and came</i> forward and questioned Jesus, saying, “Do You not answer? What is it that these men are testifying against You?”",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24816AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24816AS\"></sup>But He kept silent and did not answer. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24816AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24816AT\"></sup>Again the high priest was questioning Him, and saying to Him, “Are You the Christ, the Son of the Blessed <i>One</i>?”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>And Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am; and you shall see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24817AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24817AU\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of Power</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24817AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24817AV\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">coming with the clouds of heaven</span>.”</span>",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24818AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24818AW\"></sup>Tearing his clothes, the high priest *said, “What further need do we have of witnesses?",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>You have heard the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24819AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24819AX\"></sup>blasphemy; how does it seem to you?” And they all condemned Him to be deserving of death.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>Some began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24820AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24820AY\"></sup>spit at Him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24820AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24820AZ\"></sup>to blindfold Him, and to beat Him with their fists, and to say to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24820BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24820BA\"></sup>Prophesy!” And the officers received Him with slaps <i>in the face</i>.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24821BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24821BB\"></sup>As Peter was below in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24821BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24821BC\"></sup>the courtyard, one of the servant-girls of the high priest *came,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>and seeing Peter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24822BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24822BD\"></sup>warming himself, she looked at him and *said, “You also were with Jesus the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24822BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24822BE\"></sup>Nazarene.”",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>But he denied <i>it</i>, saying, “I neither know nor understand what you are talking about.” And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24823BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24823BF\"></sup>went out onto the porch.",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>The servant-girl saw him, and began once more to say to the bystanders, “This is <i>one</i> of them!”",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>But again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24825BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24825BG\"></sup>he denied it. And after a little while the bystanders were again saying to Peter, “Surely you are <i>one</i> of them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24825BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24825BH\"></sup>for you are a Galilean too.”",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>But he began to curse and swear, “I do not know this man you are talking about!”",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>Immediately a rooster crowed a second time. And Peter remembered how Jesus had made the remark to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24827BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24827BI\"></sup>a rooster crows twice, you will deny Me three times.”</span> And he began to weep."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24828A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24828A\"></sup>Early in the morning the chief priests with the elders and scribes and the whole <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24828B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24828B\"></sup>Council, immediately held a consultation; and binding Jesus, they led Him away and delivered Him to Pilate.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24829C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24829C\"></sup>Pilate questioned Him, “Are You the King of the Jews?” And He *answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“<i>It is as</i> you say.”</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The chief priests <i>began</i> to accuse Him harshly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Pilate questioned Him again, saying, “Do You not answer? See how many charges they bring against You!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24832D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24832D\"></sup>made no further answer; so Pilate was amazed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24833E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24833E\"></sup>Now at <i>the</i> feast he used to release for them <i>any</i> one prisoner whom they requested.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The man named Barabbas had been imprisoned with the insurrectionists who had committed murder in the insurrection.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The crowd went up and began asking him <i>to do</i> as he had been accustomed to do for them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Pilate answered them, saying, “Do you want me to release for you the King of the Jews?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For he was aware that the chief priests had handed Him over because of envy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the chief priests stirred up the crowd <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24838F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24838F\"></sup><i>to ask</i> him to release Barabbas for them instead.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Answering again, Pilate said to them, “Then what shall I do with Him whom you call the King of the Jews?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They shouted back, “Crucify Him!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Pilate said to them, “Why, what evil has He done?” But they shouted all the more, “Crucify Him!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Wishing to satisfy the crowd, Pilate released Barabbas for them, and after having Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24842G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24842G\"></sup>scourged, he handed Him over to be crucified.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24843H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24843H\"></sup>The soldiers took Him away into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24843I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24843I\"></sup>the palace (that is, the Praetorium), and they *called together the whole <i>Roman</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24843J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24843J\"></sup>cohort.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They *dressed Him up in purple, and after twisting a crown of thorns, they put it on Him;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and they began to acclaim Him, “Hail, King of the Jews!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They kept beating His head with a reed, and spitting on Him, and kneeling and bowing before Him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After they had mocked Him, they took the purple robe off Him and put His <i>own</i> garments on Him. And they *led Him out to crucify Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24848K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24848K\"></sup>They *pressed into service a passer-by coming from the country, Simon of Cyrene (the father of Alexander and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24848L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24848L\"></sup>Rufus), to bear His cross.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24849M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24849M\"></sup>Then they *brought Him to the place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24849N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24849N\"></sup>Golgotha, which is translated, Place of a Skull.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They tried to give Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24850O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24850O\"></sup>wine mixed with myrrh; but He did not take it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And they *crucified Him, and *<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24851P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24851P\"></sup>divided up His garments among themselves, casting lots for them <i>to decide</i> what each man should take.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>It was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24852Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24852Q\"></sup>third hour when they crucified Him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The inscription of the charge against Him read, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24853R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24853R\"></sup>THE KING OF THE JEWS.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They *crucified two robbers with Him, one on His right and one on His left.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>[And the Scripture was fulfilled which says, “And He was numbered with transgressors.”]",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Those passing by were hurling abuse at Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24856S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24856S\"></sup>wagging their heads, and saying, “Ha! You who <i>are going to</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24856T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24856T\"></sup>destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>save Yourself, and come down from the cross!”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>In the same way the chief priests also, along with the scribes, were mocking <i>Him</i> among themselves and saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24858U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24858U\"></sup>He saved others; He cannot save Himself.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Let <i>this</i> Christ, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24859V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24859V\"></sup>the King of Israel, now come down from the cross, so that we may see and believe!” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24859W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24859W\"></sup>Those who were crucified with Him were also insulting Him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24860X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24860X\"></sup>When the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24860Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24860Y\"></sup>sixth hour came, darkness fell over the whole land until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24860Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24860Z\"></sup>ninth hour.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24861AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24861AA\"></sup>ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24861AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24861AB\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani</span>?”</span> which is translated, <span class=\"woj\">“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">My God, My God, why have You forsaken Me</span>?”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When some of the bystanders heard it, they <i>began</i> saying, “Behold, He is calling for Elijah.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Someone ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, put it on a reed, and gave Him a drink, saying, “Let us see whether Elijah will come to take Him down.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24864AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24864AC\"></sup>And Jesus uttered a loud cry, and breathed His last.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24865AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24865AD\"></sup>And the veil of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24866AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24866AE\"></sup>When the centurion, who was standing right in front of Him, saw the way He breathed His last, he said, “Truly this man was the Son of God!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24867AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24867AF\"></sup>There were also <i>some</i> women looking on from a distance, among whom <i>were</i> Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24867AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24867AG\"></sup>the Less and Joses, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24867AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24867AH\"></sup>Salome.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When He was in Galilee, they used to follow Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24868AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24868AI\"></sup>minister to Him; and <i>there were</i> many other women who came up with Him to Jerusalem.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24869AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24869AJ\"></sup>When evening had already come, because it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24869AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24869AK\"></sup>the preparation day, that is, the day before the Sabbath,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Joseph of Arimathea came, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24870AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24870AL\"></sup>prominent member of the Council, who himself was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24870AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24870AM\"></sup>waiting for the kingdom of God; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24870AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24870AN\"></sup>gathered up courage and went in before Pilate, and asked for the body of Jesus.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Pilate wondered if He was dead by this time, and summoning the centurion, he questioned him as to whether He was already dead.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And ascertaining this from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24872AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24872AO\"></sup>the centurion, he granted the body to Joseph.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Joseph bought a linen cloth, took Him down, wrapped Him in the linen cloth and laid Him in a tomb which had been hewn out in the rock; and he rolled a stone against the entrance of the tomb.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24874AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24874AP\"></sup>Mary Magdalene and Mary the <i>mother</i> of Joses were looking on <i>to see</i> where He was laid."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24875A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24875A\"></sup>When the Sabbath was over, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24875B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24875B\"></sup>Mary Magdalene, and Mary the <i>mother</i> of James, and Salome, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24875C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24875C\"></sup>bought spices, so that they might come and anoint Him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Very early on the first day of the week, they *came to the tomb when the sun had risen.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They were saying to one another, “Who will roll away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24877D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24877D\"></sup>the stone for us from the entrance of the tomb?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Looking up, they *saw that the stone had been rolled away, although it was extremely large.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24879E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24879E\"></sup>Entering the tomb, they saw a young man sitting at the right, wearing a white robe; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24879F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24879F\"></sup>were amazed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he *said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24880G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24880G\"></sup>Do not be amazed; you are looking for Jesus the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24880H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24880H\"></sup>Nazarene, who has been crucified. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24880I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24880I\"></sup>He has risen; He is not here; behold, <i>here is</i> the place where they laid Him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But go, tell His disciples and Peter, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24881J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24881J\"></sup>He is going ahead of you to Galilee; there you will see Him, just as He told you.’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They went out and fled from the tomb, for trembling and astonishment had gripped them; and they said nothing to anyone, for they were afraid.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>[Now after He had risen early on the first day of the week, He first appeared to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24883K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24883K\"></sup>Mary Magdalene, from whom He had cast out seven demons.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24884L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24884L\"></sup>She went and reported to those who had been with Him, while they were mourning and weeping.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When they heard that He was alive and had been seen by her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24885M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24885M\"></sup>they refused to believe it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After that, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24886N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24886N\"></sup>He appeared in a different form <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24886O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24886O\"></sup>to two of them while they were walking along on their way to the country.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They went away and reported it to the others, but they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24887P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24887P\"></sup>did not believe them either.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Afterward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24888Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24888Q\"></sup>He appeared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24888R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24888R\"></sup>to the eleven themselves as they were reclining <i>at the table</i>; and He reproached them for their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24888S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24888S\"></sup>unbelief and hardness of heart, because they had not believed those who had seen Him after He had risen.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24889T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24889T\"></sup>Go into all the world and preach the gospel to all creation.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24890U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24890U\"></sup>He who has believed and has been baptized shall be saved; but he who has disbelieved shall be condemned.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These signs will accompany those who have believed: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24891V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24891V\"></sup>in My name they will cast out demons, they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24891W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24891W\"></sup>speak with new tongues;</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24892X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24892X\"></sup>pick up serpents, and if they drink any deadly <i>poison</i>, it will not hurt them; they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24892Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24892Y\"></sup>lay hands on the sick, and they will recover.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So then, when the Lord Jesus had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24893Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24893Z\"></sup>spoken to them, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24893AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24893AA\"></sup>was received up into heaven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24893AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24893AB\"></sup>sat down at the right hand of God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they went out and preached everywhere, while the Lord worked with them, and confirmed the word by the signs that followed.][<i>And they promptly reported all these instructions to Peter and his companions. And after that, Jesus Himself sent out through them from east to west the sacred and imperishable proclamation of eternal salvation.</i>]"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;